</taxonomicName>
, male, ventral view showing pilose hypostomal area, tuft of hairs on inner surface of mandible (‘t’), and oblique row of hairs on under surface of femur (‘r’); (c) 
<taxonomicName id="B3CD75EEFFCAFFBDFDD2E267FD783ABE" authorityName="Jorgensen" authorityYear="1912" box="[582,700,1398,1421]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Megachile" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="460" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obscurior">
<emphasis id="46B9D27FFFCAFFBDFDD2E267FD783ABE" box="[582,700,1398,1421]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="460">M. obscurior</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
